Science and Technology Minister Mmmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubani will launch the Mahikeng astronomy telescope on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - Management at North West University says its new telescope will put it on par with other developed South African institutions. Science and Technology Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will launch the Mahikeng astronomy telescope on Friday. The university's Takalani Nemaungani says: “This telescope will mainly be used for training for astronomy students and for research studies.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)